languageModelTools.modelDescription:
Retrieves the current Makerchip IDE layout state as a serializable object. Returns either a TabbedView state (single pane container) or FlexSplit state (split layout).

RETURNED STRUCTURE:

TabbedView state:
{
  "panes": ["Log", "Diagram", ...],  // Array of pane mnemonics in tab order
  "activePane": "Diagram"              // Currently active pane mnemonic (or null)
}

FlexSplit state (horizontal):
{
  "sides": {
    "left": <TabbedView or nested FlexSplit>,
    "right": <TabbedView or nested FlexSplit>
  },
  "splitAt": 0.5  // Split position (0.0-1.0)
}

FlexSplit state (vertical):
{
  "sides": {
    "top": <TabbedView or nested FlexSplit>,
    "bottom": <TabbedView or nested FlexSplit>
  },
  "splitAt": 0.5  // Split position (0.0-1.0)
}

Available pane mnemonics: "Log", "Nav-TLV", "Diagram", "Viz", "Waveform" (plus static panes - use makerchip_get_available_panes to see all). Note: Editor pane is NOT available in VS Code extension (VS Code provides its own editor).

Use this to: capture current layout for later restoration, understand current IDE configuration, or create modified layouts based on the current state. The returned object can be passed directly to makerchip_set_layout_state or modified before restoration.

Sets the Makerchip IDE layout from a state object. You can restore a previously saved state OR craft a custom layout defining pane arrangement, splits, tabs, and active panes.

The state is either a TabbedView (single pane container with tabs) or FlexSplit (split layout with left/right or top/bottom sides). FlexSplit sides recursively contain TabbedView or nested FlexSplit states.

Available pane mnemonics: Use makerchip_get_available_panes to get the complete list. Main panes: Log, Nav-TLV, Diagram, Viz, Waveform. Many static panes also available (tutorials, documentation, etc.). NOTE: Editor pane is NOT available (VS Code provides the editor).

EXAMPLES:

Single view with tabs: {"panes": ["Diagram", "Waveform"], "activePane": "Diagram"}

Horizontal split (Log left, Diagram+Waveform right): {"sides": {"left": {"panes": ["Log"], "activePane": "Log"}, "right": {"panes": ["Diagram", "Waveform"], "activePane": "Diagram"}}, "splitAt": 0.3}

Vertical split (Nav-TLV top, Diagram bottom): {"sides": {"top": {"panes": ["Nav-TLV"], "activePane": "Nav-TLV"}, "bottom": {"panes": ["Diagram"], "activePane": "Diagram"}}, "splitAt": 0.3}

Nested 3-way (Log left, Diagram top-right, Waveform bottom-right): {"sides": {"left": {"panes": ["Log"], "activePane": "Log"}, "right": {"sides": {"top": {"panes": ["Diagram"], "activePane": "Diagram"}, "bottom": {"panes": ["Waveform"], "activePane": "Waveform"}}, "splitAt": 0.5}}, "splitAt": 0.3}
